    <h2><a href="http://www.gablescinema.com">Coral Gables Art Cinema</a></h2>
    <p>
      The Coral Gables Art Cinema opened in October 2010 and has been named Miami’s Best Art-House
      Cinema by Miami New Times. It screens first-run and regional-premiere independent and
      international film alongside classics and festival programming. The theater was built as a
      partnership between the City of Coral Gables (which owns the building), the nonprofit Coral
      Gables Cinematheque, Inc., and Magna-Tech Electronic Company, with in-kind equipment and
      installation contributions from across the film industry. Steven Krams, MTE’s President, is
      the Cinema’s founder.
    </p>

    <h2><a href="http://www.continentalfilmlab.com">Continental Film &amp; Digital Labs</a></h2>
    <p>
      Continental Film &amp; Digital Labs is a post-production laboratory providing color correction
      and editing services, operating continuously as one of the longest-running film labs in the
      industry.
    </p>
